<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-09-0883 </DOCNO><TEXT>The purpose of the study is to identify the policy mechanisms and actionsthat represent key decisions in public-private sector cooperation inurban mass-transportation service delivery. To accomplish the study purpose,certain policy questions were explored. (1) How did the public-privaterelationship develop to its current form. (2) What is the framework ofplanning and service. (3) How is the private sector involved. (4) Whatbarriers hinder private sector involvement. (5) What practical intergovernmentalsteps would enhance private sector involvement.</TEXT></DOC>